Guide to xml files

All models start with an iodef file:
- iodef_gal_clim - for GAL physical climate configuration
- iodef_gal_clim_chem - for GAL Earth-system configuration (with chemistry)
- iodef_gal_nwp - for GAL NWP configurations up to C224
- iodef_gal_nwp_hres - for GAL NWP configurations of C896 or similar
- iodef_gal_nwp_oper - GAL NWP with operational diagnostic load
- iodef_gal_nwp_cycling - for an NWP cycling suite with data assimilation
- iodef_ls_and_jedi - for an NWP configuration giving output for JADA
- iodef_gal_nwp_coarse_aero - for an NWP config with coarse aerosol
- iodef_ral - for RAL limited area configuration
- iodef_ral_ls_and_jedi - for RAL with output for JADA
- iodef_idealised - for idealised setups
- iodef_idealised_flexchem - for exoplanet runs with flexible chemistry
- iodef_test - for test suite use only

Each iodef file is then constructed from multiple file definitions, to
determine the input and output fields

Diagnostics:
- file_def_diags_gal_clim - standard climate valnote diagnostics
- file_def_diags_gal_clim_chem - with extra chemistry diagnostics for Earth sys
- file_def_diags_gal_nwp - standard NWP case study diagnostics
- file_def_diags_oper_nwp_gl - operational NWP suite diagnostics
- file_def_diags_ver - diagnostics required for verification
- file_def_diags_var_ops - diagnostics required for VAR DA and OPS
- file_def_diags_ls_and_jedi - diagnostics required for JEDI DA
- file_def_diags_name - diagnostics required for driving NAME model
- file_def_diags_ral - standard RNS diagnostic list
- file_def_diags_ral_ls_and_jedi - diagnostics for regional DA
- file_def_initial_diags - diagnostics before the model starts timestepping
- file_def_diags_idealised - diagnostic list for idealised simulations
- file_def_diags_idealised1 - with output every timestep
- file_def_diags_flexchem - diagnostics for exoplanet chemistry runs

Pressure level diagnostic output levels are defined in axis_def_plev

Input files:
- file_def_iau - definition of the incremental analysis update file
- file_def_lbcs - lateral boundary conditions file

Ancillary files:
- file_def_ancil_main - main ancils used by all (Earth) runs
- file_def_ancil_gal - global specific ancillaries
- file_def_ancil_ral - regional specific ancillaries
- file_def_ancil_hadisst - SST & sea-ice ancils from HadISST monthly climatology
- file_def_ancil_reynolds - SST & sea-ice from daily Reynolds timeseries
- file_def_ancil_surf - SST & sea-ice from OSTIA via surf
- file_def_ancil_idealised - idealised ancils for flexible chemistry

Checkpoint-restart definition uses file_def_check_restart
